<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Disjoin" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Disjoin,</orth> 1) tr. to part, to sunder: <cit><quote>--ing hands,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.197" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 1, 197</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.197" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 1, 197</bibl> <cit><quote>scattered and --ed from fellowship,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 3.4.3" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 3</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>it --s remorse from power,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jc 2.1.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. II, 1, 18</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) intr. to part, to rid one's self: <cit><quote>till breathless he --ed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 541" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 541</bibl></cit>.
